Name: barChart

Details:

Categories: Library

Syntax:

Types:

Function:
# `Figure barChart(str title, map[str,num] facts, ChartProperty props...)`
# `Figure barChart(str title, NamedNumbers facts, ChartProperty props...)`
# `Figure barChart(str title, list[str] categories, NamedNumberSeries facts, ChartProperty props...)`

Synopsis:

Description:

Draws bar charts for given facts.

The first and second form draw a bar chart with a single bar associated with each label.

In the first form, barChart takes a map between names (label for each bar) to values (height of each bar).

In the second form, barChart uses `NamedNumbers` defined as follows:

<listing>
alias NamedNumbers  = 
       list[tuple[str name, num val] values];
</listing>

In the third form, a bar chart is drawn with multiple bars associated with each label.

A list of categories, provides a name for each group of bars. 
The data `NamedNumberSeries` is defined as follows:
       
<listing>
alias NamedNumberSeries =
       list[tuple[str name, list[num] values]];
</listing>

Examples:
<figure b1.png>
import vis::Chart;
chart = barChart("Fruit Inventory (using vertical bars)", 
                 [<"apple", 10>, <"pear", 20>, <"kiwi", 30>],
                 xLabel("Fruit"), yLabel("In Stock"));
render(chart);
</figure>
